# Environment Variables for Real-time Markdown Previewer

This file outlines the environment variables used by the Real-time Markdown Previewer application.
These variables are typically loaded from a `.env` file in development and configured in the deployment environment for production.

For client-side React applications, environment variables must be prefixed with `REACT_APP_` to be exposed to the browser bundle.

---

# Core Application Configuration

# REACT_APP_MARKDOWN_PREVIEWER_TITLE
# Sets the title displayed in the application header or browser tab.
# Default: "Real-time Markdown Previewer"
REACT_APP_MARKDOWN_PREVIEWER_TITLE="Real-time Markdown Previewer"

# REACT_APP_DEFAULT_MARKDOWN_TEXT
# Initial Markdown text to load in the editor when the application starts.
# Useful for demonstrations or providing a starting point for users.
# Default: "# Hello Markdown!\n\nType your **Markdown** here to see a *live* preview.\n\n- Item 1\n- Item 2\n\n```javascript\nconsole.log('Code blocks are supported!');\n```"
REACT_APP_DEFAULT_MARKDOWN_TEXT="# Hello Markdown!\n\nType your **Markdown** here to see a *live* preview.\n\n- Item 1\n- Item 2\n\n```javascript\nconsole.log('Code blocks are supported!');\n```"

---

# Cross-Service Integration (Microservices Context)

# These variables are for demonstrating integration with other services
# within the larger ecosystem, such as the "Personal Recipe Book & Search".

# REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL
# Base URL for a generic backend API that this application might interact with.
# This could be a shared gateway or a specific backend for the previewer itself
# if it were to store user preferences, history, etc.
# Example: http://localhost:3001/api
# REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=

# REACT_APP_RECIPE_SERVICE_URL
# The base URL for the "Personal Recipe Book & Search" service.
# This would be used if the Markdown Previewer needed to fetch or link to recipes,
# for example, to embed recipe cards or provide recipe search functionality within the markdown.
# Example: http://localhost:3002/recipes
# REACT_APP_RECIPE_SERVICE_URL=

# REACT_APP_FEATURE_FLAG_EMBED_RECIPES
# A feature flag to enable or disable the functionality to embed recipes
# from the Personal Recipe Book service directly into the Markdown preview.
# Set to 'true' to enable, 'false' to disable.
# Default: false
# REACT_APP_FEATURE_FLAG_EMBED_RECIPES=false